Merge OVRUI into react-vr repo

Summary: Large diff moving the OVRUI contents into the react-vr repo, to create a single repo on GitHub. In updating all of our Oculus and GH scripts and tests, I've also updated Prettier, which involved a pass across the React VR codebase to clean up any lint noise. In both internal and public setups, React VR is able to locate the OVRUI codebase, using our master branch instead of the latest package from npm, which should improve testing.

fbshipit-source-id: f6cd9d2

GLTF2 static model loaders

Summary:
Add loading of gltf2 models using the model registry.

Downloading the model is async but parsing the model is blocking. we will need to investigate the best way to reuse three.js loaders with incremental parsing

Example usage:

```
<Model
  style={{
    transform: [
      {translate: [-1, 0, -1]},
      {scale: 0.2},
      {rotateY: -this.state.rotation},
    ],
  }}
  source={{
    gltf2: asset('duck.gltf'),
  }}/>
```

Script to easily bump version numbers, update master branch to latest versions

Summary:
introduces a new script to simplify the deployment process. Running `node scripts/bump-versions.js 1.4.0` will increment all of the core packages to v1.4.0, update their cross-dependencies, and update the package.json file generated in new projects, incrementing the CLI by a patch version.

I'm also catching up the master branch to the latest versions that were previously deployed from launch branches. These changes never made it back into master.
